---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 122
By: Sister Consolata
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Sacrifice and Suffering=The Divine Allopathy
---
‘Do not think that the afflictions of the world leave Me indifferent. I love
souls and I want to save them. To attain My end I use hardship, but it is
through pure mercy. In times of abundance, souls forget Me and are lost,
whereas in distress they turn to Me and are saved.’
